Hi Emil Skogsund,
On Day 4 of Langfuse Launch Week #2, we're shining a spotlight on an often overlooked but critical element of great developer
experience: Documentation.
 


📒 New Langfuse Docs

At Langfuse, we believe that documentation is product. Today, we're excited to release brand-new, comprehensive documentation
pages for Datasets [https://langfuse.com/docs/datasets], Experimentation [https://langfuse.com/docs/datasets], and Evaluation
[https://langfuse.com/docs/scores].
We've completely rebuilt our docs to be more thorough and user-friendly than ever before, helping teams accelerate the development
of their LLM applications.
🔍 What's New?
 * Guidance on using Datasets and Evals: Dive deep into the effective evaluation of your LLM applications during development.

 * Introduction to Core Data Models: Get to know our foundational data structures—datasets, experiment runs, and scores.

 * End-to-End Examples: Try common workflows with our example notebooks.

 
As the Langfuse community continues to grow (latest metrics
[https://langfuse.com/blog/2024-11-most-used-oss-llmops#detailed-metrics]), best-in-class documentation has become essential for
teams adopting Langfuse.
To celebrate Launch Week, we've also summarized all the documentation improvements
[https://langfuse.com/changelog/2024-11-21-all-new-datasets-and-evals-documentation#learn-more-about-documentation-at-langfuse]
we've made over the past year. We think it's an interesting read and welcome any feedback you may have!
🕹️ Learn more: Check out our changelog [https://langfuse.com/changelog/2024-11-21-all-new-datasets-and-evals-documentation] to
learn what's new, and dive into our docs here [https://langfuse.com/docs].
 


🅿️ Langfuse on Product Hunt

We are launching the biggest new features tomorrow on Product Hunt [https://langfuse.com/ph] – we cannot wait to show this to you
and get your feedback!
 
To support the launch, you can set a reminder here [https://langfuse.com/ph] – we really appreciate your support as this helps us
to spread the word and grow the community.
 
 


⏮️ All releases of Launch Week #2

 * 🔻 Day 0: Langfuse Prompt Management [https://langfuse.com/docs/prompts/get-started] now integrates natively with the Vercel AI
   SDK. Version and release prompts in Langfuse, use them via Vercel AI SDK, monitor metrics in Langfuse. (Twitter
   [https://x.com/marcklingen/status/1858145579789943233?sF], Changelog
   [https://langfuse.com/changelog/2024-11-17-vercel-ai-sdk-prompt-mgmt])

 * 🌓 Day 1: Langfuse Datasets [https://langfuse.com/docs/datasets/overview] now offers a powerful comparison view for dataset
   experiment runs. It's perfect for teams iterating on their AI applications with different prompts, models, or parameters who
   want to quickly see the results of a change in a side-by-side with their benchmark version. (Twitter
   [https://x.com/MarcKlingen/status/1858539441813410139], Changelog
   [https://langfuse.com/changelog/2024-11-18-dataset-runs-comparison-view])

 * ⚖️ Day 2: Datasets in Langfuse allow you to create test sets and benchmarks to evaluate the performance of your LLM
   application. Until now, Dataset Experiments required custom evaluations added via SDKs or APIs. Starting today, you can use
   LLM-as-a-Judge Evaluators on the Datasets you maintain in Langfuse. (Twitter
   [https://x.com/MarcKlingen/status/1858987480411730280], Changelog
   [https://langfuse.com/changelog/2024-11-19-llm-as-a-judge-for-datasets])

 * 🎨  Day 3: Langfuse Tracing now offers full multi-modal support [https://langfuse.com/docs/tracing-features/multi-modality],
   including images, audio files, and attachments! This highly requested feature allows you to integrate media such as images
   (PNG, JPG, WEBP), audio files (MPEG, MP3, WAV), and documents (PDF, plain text) directly into your traces, enhancing your
   development and monitoring workflow in Langfuse. (Twitter [https://x.com/MarcKlingen/status/1859288134330069417], Changelog
   [https://langfuse.com/changelog/2024-11-20-full-multi-modal-images-audio-attachments])https://langfuse.com/blog/2024-11-17-launch-week-2#day-3

